channel.title: Is 5.84.95.199 a local ip?
channel.description:
is 5.84.95.199 a local ip? I have Hamachi and No-IP but it shows up and lets me log in to that ip address. I want to mask my Serve ip (5.84.95.199) to "superman20.servegame.com" i already have the superman20 server address set up in my no-ip account and the port is opened but it yet does not let me join.
So, since i cant mask it... i want to know if 5.84.95.199 is a local ip. Is it?

item.title: Is 5.84.95.199 a local ip?
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

televator0 = n00blet

that IP address is your internet IP. IT IS NOT A LOCAL IP. When you make a new no-ip, then you put in the name in redirect/host. Then you select the domain you want. Then put that IP address (the one that you saide above ^) into the text box which requires an IP address. Then save it. If your router is port forwarding then this should work all fine&dandy. If it is not, there is not point of using no-ip (if you dont have a router, if you do but it’s not port forwarding, then look at my tutorial on server building.) Also, I do not know if you use no-ip as a redirect with Hamachi (I don’t know becaue Hamachi SUCKS because its peer to peer :mad: )
